<item>
            <title>[LU-19421] Add deny_mount into the scope of child_raise_privileges for child nodemaps</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19421</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Nodemap property &lt;tt&gt;deny_mount&lt;/tt&gt; is out of the scope of &lt;tt&gt;child_raise_privileges&lt;/tt&gt;, which means child nodemap can change it to 0 (allows mount) even when its parent has it set to 1 (deny_mount). We should consider adding &lt;tt&gt;deny_mount&lt;/tt&gt; into the scope of &lt;tt&gt;child_raise_privileges&lt;/tt&gt; so that child nodemap cannot change it if it is not allowed by &lt;tt&gt;child_raise_privileges&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
